tool.name: LTSSplitter

param.name: LTSCount
param.dialogReference: Number of files to separate the LTS into.

param.name: RunoffFile
param.dialogReference: Optional: Input runoff file (extension .CRF) to duplicate. Each network simulation to be run in parallel requires a separate runoff file, which this creates.

param.name: database
param.displayname: Mike Urban database (for duplicating network simulations)
param.dialogReference: Optional: Input Mike Urban database - fill in if you want to duplicate anetwork simulation in it to be used for parallel processing.

param.name: network_simulation
param.dialogReference: Optional: Input network simulation - it's the simulation from your mike urban simulation that you want to run in parallel. Requires input mike urban database to be filled in.

tool.summary:
Split LTS file into a number of separate LTS files. Suitable for parallel processing.

Optional:

Duplicates the runoff simulation file.

Duplicates a selected network simulation.
